# LLM wiki (docs layout)

These rules apply to the **Pitchd default** wiki tree: **`docs/llm-wiki/`** beside
a Rails app. Canonical workflow: **`skills/maintaining-llm-wiki/SKILL.md`**.

## Boundaries

- **`docs/llm-wiki/raw/**`** — Treat as **human-curated, agent-read-only**. Do not
  edit, rename, or delete raw sources unless the user explicitly asked for that
  housekeeping in this turn.
- **Wiki pages** (elsewhere under `docs/llm-wiki/`) — Agent may create and edit
  to integrate knowledge, cross-link, and record contradictions.
- **`SCHEMA.md`** — Co-owned contract; change only when aligning with the user on
  structure or workflow.

## File responsibilities

| File | Rule |
|------|------|
| `index.md` | Stay in sync with wiki pages: every substantive page listed with a one-line summary; update when adding/removing pages. |
| `log.md` | **Append-only** for ingest/query/lint events; use consistent entry headers so logs stay greppable. |
| Topic/entity pages | Prefer stable filenames; when renaming, update inbound links and `index.md`. |

## Style

- Prefer **relative links** between wiki pages.
- When new information **contradicts** an existing page, **update both** (or add
  a contradiction note) — do not silently delete old claims without trace.
- Keep **Rails app code** out of this tree unless the user asked for embedded
  snippets; this directory is for **compiled knowledge**, not application source.

## Relationship to Rails work

Wiki edits here are **documentation** — they do **not** replace
`rules/testing.mdc`, `implementing-pitchd-rails`, or app implementation tasks.
